==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Macron
<hw>Ma"cron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/
long.]</ety> <fld>(Pron.)</fld> <def>A short, straight, horizontal mark
[-], placed over vowels to denote that they are to be pronounced with a
long sound; as, <examp>⟦amac⟧</examp>, in <examp>d⟦amac⟧me</examp>;
<examp>⟦emac⟧</examp>, in <examp>s⟦emac⟧am</examp>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> macrotone.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Macropetalous</ent>⟦br⟧
